7.1 Focus on Lincoln

The Bridge Behavioral Health: A nationally accredited non-profit, The Bridge offers a full continuum of care, including medically supervised withdrawal, residential treatment, and recovery support services. They are a key provider for those utilizing Medicaid and state funding.61
Bryan Independence Center: As a hospital-based facility, Bryan offers comprehensive medical oversight, 24/7 nursing coverage, and a complete range of care levels from detox to outpatient. They have distinct programs for adults and adolescents.69
CenterPointe: With a mission to help people with mental health and substance use disorders achieve recovery, CenterPointe provides a wide array of services including residential and outpatient treatment, crisis response, and critical housing support.70
St. Monica's Behavioral Health for Women: This facility provides gender-specific, trauma-informed care for women, including specialized residential programs for mothers with children and Native American mothers.63
Houses of Hope of Nebraska: Operating since 1962, Houses of Hope provides a transitional halfway house environment for men and a short-term residential program (Touchstone) for both men and women.63

7.2 Focus on Omaha

Nebraska Medicine: The academic medical center offers sophisticated, evidence-based care for addiction and co-occurring mental health disorders, with a multidisciplinary team of board-certified addiction psychiatrists and therapists.74
Valley Hope of Omaha: This facility provides flexible but intensive outpatient and partial hospitalization programs, integrating 12-Step philosophy with clinical methods like CBT and MAT.75
ARCH Halfway House: A long-standing community pillar, ARCH has provided transitional housing and treatment services for men since 1972, focusing on a therapeutic community and life skills development.77
The 1212 House: This organization offers a structured and safe sober living environment for men, emphasizing accountability, personal responsibility, and the development of life skills.79
Siena Francis House Miracles Program: This CARF-accredited program provides free, long-term residential treatment based on the 12-Step model specifically for individuals experiencing homelessness.80
Northpoint Nebraska: A 44-bed inpatient facility offering detox and rehabilitation with a focus on evidence-based therapies and dual diagnosis treatment.82

7.3 Services for Adolescents

Finding appropriate care for adolescents is a specific challenge. In addition to the services offered at Bryan Independence Center, several providers specialize in youth treatment. Imagine Omaha offers partial hospitalization (PHP) and intensive outpatient (IOP) programs for teens aged 12-17 struggling with mental health and co-occurring substance use.84 Evolve Treatment Centers, while not based in Nebraska, serves the area and offers high-caliber residential treatment for adolescents specializing in DBT and CBT.87

